1
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:34,520
=Lady Liberty=

2
00:01:35,020 --> 00:01:37,940
=Episode 12=

3
00:01:43,340 --> 00:01:44,020
Fragile

4
00:01:44,700 --> 00:01:45,500
or Naobaijin?

5
00:01:48,460 --> 00:01:50,260
For these five who hadn't signed before,

6
00:01:50,260 --> 00:01:51,940
it's understandable they got poached.

7
00:01:52,400 --> 00:01:54,580
As for the rest who signed
but didn't pay the deposit,

8
00:01:54,733 --> 00:01:56,380
if they start backing out with excuses,

9
00:01:56,555 --> 00:01:58,660
it will affect Zhiyuan's
final assessment of you.

10
00:02:06,700 --> 00:02:07,100
Then,

11
00:02:08,140 --> 00:02:08,700
if...

12
00:02:09,060 --> 00:02:10,740
Zhiyuan doesn't give us the money...

13
00:02:12,500 --> 00:02:14,380
Does that mean
Chenxing is going to shut down?

14
00:02:21,780 --> 00:02:22,300
Well,

15
00:02:25,380 --> 00:02:27,100
didn't you already reach out to Gu Yan?

16
00:02:27,980 --> 00:02:28,888
What did he say?

17
00:02:29,180 --> 00:02:30,580
I told him, but he hasn't replied.

18
00:02:32,100 --> 00:02:33,780
I thought he didn't
bother replying to me

19
00:02:33,780 --> 00:02:35,180
and went straight to you instead.

20
00:02:35,900 --> 00:02:37,488
I didn't get any message from him.

21
00:02:37,577 --> 00:02:38,844
What time did you send it?

22
00:02:39,260 --> 00:02:40,660
Around 7 PM.

23
00:02:43,860 --> 00:02:44,900
Should I go ask him?

24
00:02:45,511 --> 00:02:46,500
I'll contact him myself.

25
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:47,688
You two get some sleep.

26
00:03:17,666 --> 00:03:19,180
(Cai Zhangzhu: Chenxing in crisis.)

27
00:03:59,380 --> 00:03:59,860
Heading out?

28
00:04:00,066 --> 00:04:01,355
I'm going to check on Gu Yan.

29
00:04:01,377 --> 00:04:03,480
He didn't answer
my calls or reply to my messages.

30
00:04:03,580 --> 00:04:05,377
At this hour, he's probably still awake.

31
00:04:05,422 --> 00:04:06,711
Didn't he submit his manuscript?

32
00:04:06,820 --> 00:04:07,260
He did.

33
00:04:07,940 --> 00:04:08,940
Then why worry so much?

34
00:04:09,900 --> 00:04:11,100
Just looking out for my author.

35
00:04:47,900 --> 00:04:49,100
Darn you!

36
00:04:50,740 --> 00:04:51,740
Darn you!

37
00:04:51,740 --> 00:04:52,660
What are you doing?

38
00:04:54,300 --> 00:04:54,980
Stop it!

39
00:04:58,100 --> 00:04:58,540
Gu Yan!

40
00:05:01,020 --> 00:05:01,940
What are you two doing?

41
00:05:02,060 --> 00:05:03,044
I'll call the police.

42
00:05:07,260 --> 00:05:07,820
Go ahead.

43
00:05:08,780 --> 00:05:09,620
Call them now!

44
00:05:10,266 --> 00:05:12,660
When they get here,
I'll say you forced yourself on San Mei!

45
00:05:14,940 --> 00:05:15,980
Holding her counts as that?

46
00:05:16,740 --> 00:05:17,980
Holding her counts as that?

47
00:05:18,180 --> 00:05:19,180
Do you even know the law?

48
00:05:19,180 --> 00:05:20,700
You were the one who got her drunk.

49
00:05:20,900 --> 00:05:22,622
When have I not had her drink with me?

50
00:05:22,700 --> 00:05:24,180
When have I not had her drink with me?

51
00:05:24,644 --> 00:05:25,660
What are you two doing?

52
00:05:25,660 --> 00:05:26,380
Stop it!

53
00:05:26,660 --> 00:05:27,700
What are you doing?

54
00:05:28,540 --> 00:05:29,260
Stop it.

55
00:05:32,100 --> 00:05:32,980
I'm telling you,

56
00:05:33,820 --> 00:05:35,340
when you're around, I ask you to drink.

57
00:05:35,820 --> 00:05:36,460
When you're not,

58
00:05:36,460 --> 00:05:38,066
does that mean we can't drink together?

59
00:05:38,540 --> 00:05:40,260
San Mei came over
and asked me to hold her.

60
00:05:43,133 --> 00:05:44,955
You weren't at the internet cafe,

61
00:05:45,100 --> 00:05:46,355
and it was just the two of us.

62
00:05:46,820 --> 00:05:48,380
If I didn't comfort her, who would?

63
00:05:54,200 --> 00:05:55,444
That's enough, Gu Yan.

64
00:05:55,740 --> 00:05:56,580
Stop it, Gu Yan!

65
00:06:04,220 --> 00:06:05,111
I'm telling you,

66
00:06:07,740 --> 00:06:08,860
I do like San Mei.

67
00:06:10,044 --> 00:06:11,740
Back when you two liked each other,

68
00:06:11,740 --> 00:06:13,066
I had no place to step in.

69
00:06:14,044 --> 00:06:15,888
Now you've moved on to something better,

70
00:06:16,740 --> 00:06:17,980
you don't want her, but I do.

71
00:06:18,260 --> 00:06:20,260
Me confessing to her
makes perfect sense.

72
00:06:20,888 --> 00:06:23,100
Confessing to her is reasonable,
no matter how you look at it.

73
00:06:23,140 --> 00:06:24,688
The one who's out of line is you.

74
00:06:24,820 --> 00:06:25,540
Get out.

75
00:06:26,220 --> 00:06:27,540
Get out!

76
00:06:31,900 --> 00:06:32,780
Wanting more

77
00:06:34,100 --> 00:06:35,180
than one can have.

78
00:06:35,700 --> 00:06:36,860
That's exactly you.

79
00:06:39,100 --> 00:06:39,540
Gu Yan.

80
00:06:40,700 --> 00:06:41,140
Stop it.

81
00:06:41,140 --> 00:06:42,380
If you ever treat San Mei badly,

82
00:06:42,980 --> 00:06:44,100
I'll kill you.

83
00:06:44,711 --> 00:06:45,933
That's enough, Gu Yan.

84
00:06:46,660 --> 00:06:47,780
I'm not like you!

85
00:06:52,820 --> 00:06:53,580
Come in.

86
00:07:03,780 --> 00:07:04,380
Sit down.

87
00:07:15,740 --> 00:07:17,580
The three of us came
to Shanghai together.

88
00:07:19,460 --> 00:07:20,340
All these years,

89
00:07:21,133 --> 00:07:22,777
I haven't had any other friends,

90
00:07:23,900 --> 00:07:25,100
just these two.

91
00:07:27,500 --> 00:07:29,100
And now I've lost even them.

92
00:07:35,700 --> 00:07:36,844
Put some ice on it first.

93
00:07:40,940 --> 00:07:42,260
You should head back. I'm fine.

94
00:07:44,260 --> 00:07:46,300
You've always told me to play less.

95
00:07:47,740 --> 00:07:48,740
I won't play anymore.

96
00:07:49,300 --> 00:07:50,333
I'll focus on writing.

97
00:08:00,100 --> 00:08:01,700
You can treat me as your friend.

98
00:08:05,220 --> 00:08:06,755
Lin Zhanqiao, you're not my friend.

99
00:08:07,620 --> 00:08:08,500
I'm your boss.

100
00:08:09,066 --> 00:08:10,577
But I can be your friend too.

101
00:08:13,740 --> 00:08:15,420
You're already everything I have here.

102
00:08:21,660 --> 00:08:23,860
No one can ever be
everything to someone.

103
00:08:25,420 --> 00:08:26,288
People are different.

104
00:08:26,860 --> 00:08:27,820
What we go through

105
00:08:28,780 --> 00:08:30,020
is always changing.

106
00:08:31,580 --> 00:08:33,380
I hope I can stay with you all the time.

107
00:08:41,860 --> 00:08:42,980
Editors and authors

108
00:08:42,980 --> 00:08:44,340
rarely stay together for long.

109
00:08:45,222 --> 00:08:46,466
If the writing is too good,

110
00:08:46,780 --> 00:08:47,888
it's hard to stay together.

111
00:08:48,422 --> 00:08:49,555
If the writing isn't good,

112
00:08:50,060 --> 00:08:51,300
it's even harder.

113
00:08:59,777 --> 00:09:01,577
I'll hold on to you no matter what.

114
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:06,866
You're just afraid of being alone.

115
00:09:07,620 --> 00:09:08,820
But you won't be alone.

116
00:09:11,133 --> 00:09:12,044
I'm heading back now.

117
00:09:12,200 --> 00:09:13,688
There's a meeting early tomorrow.

118
00:09:13,860 --> 00:09:14,980
Call me if anything comes up.

119
00:09:15,540 --> 00:09:16,860
Can you stay with me a bit longer?

120
00:09:20,580 --> 00:09:21,740
Just ten minutes.

121
00:09:55,380 --> 00:09:57,980
(Cai Zhangzhu: Chenxing in crisis!
1 hour ago)

122
00:09:59,220 --> 00:09:59,860
What happened?

123
00:10:19,780 --> 00:10:20,180
Hello?

124
00:10:21,460 --> 00:10:22,380
You were asleep?

125
00:10:22,555 --> 00:10:24,266
It's only twelve,
and you're already asleep?

126
00:10:24,300 --> 00:10:25,660
Tell me, what happened to Chenxing?

127
00:10:27,580 --> 00:10:28,380
I'll come find you.

128
00:10:28,500 --> 00:10:29,422
Let's talk in person.

129
00:10:30,580 --> 00:10:31,660
Come downstairs quietly.

130
00:10:31,780 --> 00:10:32,955
Don't let your boss know.

131
00:11:17,860 --> 00:11:18,420
Come out.

132
00:11:23,780 --> 00:11:24,977
What are you doing here?

133
00:11:27,260 --> 00:11:28,100
Surprise.

134
00:11:30,460 --> 00:11:31,220
What's going on?

135
00:11:31,533 --> 00:11:33,511
I'm not here for you.
I'm looking for Zhangzhu.

136
00:11:33,622 --> 00:11:35,688
A friend of mine ran into
some renovation issues.

137
00:11:35,777 --> 00:11:37,755
I wanted to ask if
Zhangzhu's dad could help.

138
00:11:37,820 --> 00:11:40,000
What's so urgent that
it can't wait till morning?

139
00:11:40,340 --> 00:11:41,820
Well, I'm not too sure either.

140
00:11:41,820 --> 00:11:43,355
Something about
leaks or electrical issues.

141
00:11:43,444 --> 00:11:44,266
Anyway, it's urgent.

142
00:11:44,500 --> 00:11:45,060
Sorry.

143
00:11:47,020 --> 00:11:48,100
Ms. Lin, you're here, too.

144
00:11:49,620 --> 00:11:49,980
Then,

145
00:11:50,260 --> 00:11:52,220
Mr. He Han,
you can just ask Ms. Lin directly.

146
00:11:56,260 --> 00:11:57,820
I'm here for you. Why would I ask her?

147
00:11:58,155 --> 00:11:59,444
Let's leave it for tonight.

148
00:11:59,488 --> 00:12:01,377
- We'll talk tomorrow.
- What did he want with you?

149
00:12:04,100 --> 00:12:05,060
Two days off...

150
00:12:05,060 --> 00:12:05,820
I'm asking you.

151
00:12:05,820 --> 00:12:07,244
Why are you looking at him?

152
00:12:11,140 --> 00:12:11,860
He just

153
00:12:12,420 --> 00:12:14,820
asked about the company lately.

154
00:12:23,660 --> 00:12:24,540
So you've been

155
00:12:24,540 --> 00:12:26,020
telling him everything

156
00:12:26,020 --> 00:12:27,140
about our company, right?

157
00:12:27,311 --> 00:12:28,140
No, that's not it.

158
00:12:28,260 --> 00:12:29,200
It's not her fault.

159
00:12:29,340 --> 00:12:29,900
I asked.

160
00:12:32,533 --> 00:12:33,580
Well, that clears it up.

161
00:12:33,580 --> 00:12:34,660
Do we have to talk out here?

162
00:12:34,660 --> 00:12:35,533
Let's go upstairs.

163
00:12:36,220 --> 00:12:37,020
Upstairs?

164
00:12:37,180 --> 00:12:37,860
Go.

165
00:12:37,980 --> 00:12:38,740
Let's go.

166
00:12:39,180 --> 00:12:39,580
Come on.

167
00:12:48,355 --> 00:12:50,111
Mr. He Han, I'll get you some slippers.

168
00:13:04,660 --> 00:13:06,060
I'll head to bed first.

169
00:13:06,060 --> 00:13:06,700
You two talk.

170
00:13:06,820 --> 00:13:07,140
Alright.

171
00:13:07,488 --> 00:13:08,577
- Go on.
- Good night.

172
00:13:08,733 --> 00:13:09,660
Good night, Ms. Lin.

173
00:13:10,980 --> 00:13:11,580
So sleepy.

174
00:13:16,422 --> 00:13:17,866
What are you looking at?

175
00:13:19,066 --> 00:13:20,520
Didn't get yourself a new boyfriend?

176
00:13:26,100 --> 00:13:27,860
What were you asking Zhangzhu about?

177
00:13:31,340 --> 00:13:32,340
I heard your company

178
00:13:32,577 --> 00:13:34,177
ran into financial trouble.

179
00:13:35,222 --> 00:13:36,688
There was a bit of an incident.

180
00:13:36,820 --> 00:13:37,777
We're handling it.

181
00:13:38,180 --> 00:13:39,860
Zhao Lanxin and
Ling Yikai were behind it?

182
00:13:41,220 --> 00:13:42,700
Working with new authors

183
00:13:42,822 --> 00:13:44,444
is usually straightforward,

184
00:13:45,288 --> 00:13:46,955
and the investment isn't high.

185
00:13:48,140 --> 00:13:49,580
It's always been a competitive game.

186
00:13:54,755 --> 00:13:57,022
Now the people are gone,
and the money's gone.

187
00:13:57,600 --> 00:13:58,888
What are you planning to do?

188
00:14:06,340 --> 00:14:07,380
Why hesitate?

189
00:14:08,860 --> 00:14:10,300
I wouldn't harm you.

190
00:14:15,100 --> 00:14:16,740
Honestly, I don't know what to do yet.

191
00:14:17,900 --> 00:14:19,780
It only came up today.

192
00:14:23,220 --> 00:14:24,420
I need time to sort it out.

193
00:14:26,740 --> 00:14:27,860
Worst case,

194
00:14:30,900 --> 00:14:31,860
I'll just

195
00:14:32,340 --> 00:14:33,180
shut Chenxing down,

196
00:14:34,660 --> 00:14:35,540
as Dai Shan did,

197
00:14:36,940 --> 00:14:38,466
take one or two authors with me,

198
00:14:41,420 --> 00:14:42,180
and start over.

199
00:14:58,511 --> 00:15:00,100
Is there anything I can help with?

200
00:15:05,820 --> 00:15:06,460
I mean it.

201
00:15:07,060 --> 00:15:07,700
Actually,

202
00:15:12,740 --> 00:15:14,100
you've already left Chenxing.

203
00:15:18,260 --> 00:15:19,300
You don't need

204
00:15:20,700 --> 00:15:21,780
to worry about it anymore.

205
00:15:23,780 --> 00:15:24,620
Besides,

206
00:15:25,860 --> 00:15:27,340
Gu Yan is technically your competitor.

207
00:15:28,940 --> 00:15:30,020
You shouldn't be helping me.

208
00:15:31,340 --> 00:15:31,900
First of all,

209
00:15:32,620 --> 00:15:34,020
Gu Yan isn't my rival.

210
00:15:34,940 --> 00:15:35,888
He's not on my level.

211
00:15:37,420 --> 00:15:37,900
Second,

212
00:15:38,540 --> 00:15:39,540
I left Chenxing

213
00:15:39,540 --> 00:15:40,780
because you sold me out.

214
00:15:43,140 --> 00:15:43,860
No matter what,

215
00:15:46,540 --> 00:15:48,380
I never expected
Zhao Lanxin and Ling Yikai

216
00:15:48,500 --> 00:15:49,700
to kick you while you were down

217
00:15:49,844 --> 00:15:50,977
and setting up something new.

218
00:15:51,020 --> 00:15:52,777
Pushing you and Chenxing to this point

219
00:15:54,666 --> 00:15:56,511
isn't something I wanted to see either.

220
00:16:13,780 --> 00:16:15,580
The money Zhiyuan Investment pulled out

221
00:16:17,780 --> 00:16:19,020
is crucial to me.

222
00:16:22,900 --> 00:16:24,380
In fact, over the past few months,

223
00:16:27,300 --> 00:16:28,540
Chenxing's financial situation

224
00:16:30,180 --> 00:16:32,460
has been far worse
than it looks on the surface.

225
00:16:47,540 --> 00:16:48,180
Are you hungry?

226
00:16:48,488 --> 00:16:50,155
I'll take you out for a late-night bite.

227
00:17:32,755 --> 00:17:34,066
What do you feel like eating?

228
00:17:37,060 --> 00:17:37,700
Forget it.

229
00:17:39,140 --> 00:17:41,088
Then let's skip food and
grab a drink somewhere.

230
00:17:45,980 --> 00:17:46,620
I think

231
00:17:48,980 --> 00:17:50,300
there's nothing in particular

232
00:17:50,780 --> 00:17:52,300
I really need your help with.

233
00:17:54,940 --> 00:17:56,380
Since we finally broke up,

234
00:17:58,420 --> 00:17:59,660
and we've both started

235
00:17:59,660 --> 00:18:01,340
new lives and new jobs,

236
00:18:05,244 --> 00:18:07,800
we shouldn't interfere
with each other anymore.

237
00:18:09,740 --> 00:18:11,222
I'm just concerned about you.

238
00:18:12,266 --> 00:18:13,866
You can still care after a breakup.

239
00:18:14,244 --> 00:18:16,180
If you're going to trust someone,
you might as well trust me.

240
00:18:16,180 --> 00:18:16,911
Right?

241
00:18:17,860 --> 00:18:19,340
And what do you mean by "finally"?

242
00:18:20,220 --> 00:18:21,500
Wasn't it just a random fight

243
00:18:21,500 --> 00:18:23,088
and then we broke up for no reason?

244
00:18:33,100 --> 00:18:33,580
Yeah.

245
00:18:34,580 --> 00:18:36,500
Maybe it felt random to you,

246
00:18:40,540 --> 00:18:41,420
but to me,

247
00:18:45,220 --> 00:18:46,220
it was hard-earned.

248
00:18:57,900 --> 00:18:59,340
So let's keep our distance.

249
00:19:01,933 --> 00:19:03,311
Thanks for your concern.

250
00:19:09,955 --> 00:19:11,420
Are you afraid that if you get moved,

251
00:19:11,420 --> 00:19:12,888
you'll regret breaking up with me?

252
00:19:22,380 --> 00:19:24,300
If you hadn't said that last line,

253
00:19:26,820 --> 00:19:27,740
after I went upstairs,

254
00:19:28,511 --> 00:19:30,577
I might've actually
thought better of you.

255
00:20:13,540 --> 00:20:16,100
♪I keep asking myself♪

256
00:20:17,980 --> 00:20:21,380
♪What it is I should become♪

257
00:20:23,300 --> 00:20:32,820
♪To follow what my heart truly wants♪

258
00:20:41,660 --> 00:20:44,500
♪Like a drifting dandelion♪

259
00:20:46,660 --> 00:20:47,740
(What a long day.)

260
00:20:49,900 --> 00:20:52,540
(In the end,
I can only bear everything myself.)

261
00:20:55,060 --> 00:20:56,900
(I appreciate He Han's kindness.)

262
00:20:58,540 --> 00:21:00,220
(He has his own battles to fight.)

263
00:21:02,580 --> 00:21:03,220
(A day.)

264
00:21:05,060 --> 00:21:05,700
(A year.)

265
00:21:07,580 --> 00:21:08,140
(A lifetime.)

266
00:21:10,940 --> 00:21:12,820
(Who isn't fighting alone?)

267
00:21:15,900 --> 00:21:18,140
(How can I stop fighting alone?)

268
00:21:19,180 --> 00:21:25,540
♪Across fields of blooms,
a boat awaits me♪

269
00:21:28,780 --> 00:21:30,580
(Cai Zhangzhu: Can I see you tomorrow?)

270
00:21:33,660 --> 00:21:38,460
♪Not waiting for calm to come♪

271
00:21:38,460 --> 00:21:41,700
(I need to see you, too.)

272
00:21:42,333 --> 00:21:43,266
Go on, hit him again.

273
00:21:43,511 --> 00:21:45,422
Beat him to death, and I'll be with you.

274
00:21:48,133 --> 00:21:49,177
The same goes for you.

275
00:21:49,200 --> 00:21:50,800
Kill him and you'll be even more famous.

276
00:21:50,860 --> 00:21:52,533
More famous than writing online fiction.

277
00:21:52,660 --> 00:21:54,990
Once you're in prison,
you'll have plenty of time to write.

278
00:21:55,288 --> 00:21:57,177
Wasn't I angry because
he was messing with you?

279
00:21:57,422 --> 00:21:58,580
The way he talked about...

280
00:21:58,666 --> 00:22:00,755
Who did I mess with?
You think I'd mess with San Mei?

281
00:22:00,820 --> 00:22:01,940
Then if I say you did,

282
00:22:02,220 --> 00:22:02,860
shouldn't you be

283
00:22:02,860 --> 00:22:04,060
slapping yourself in the face?

284
00:22:04,380 --> 00:22:05,260
I'm a grown-up.

285
00:22:05,260 --> 00:22:06,990
I'm not someone
people can just push around.

286
00:22:08,700 --> 00:22:09,460
Listen carefully.

287
00:22:11,220 --> 00:22:11,620
Er Jiu,

288
00:22:13,180 --> 00:22:14,380
I haven't said I'd be with you.

289
00:22:14,940 --> 00:22:16,460
Even if I had considered it,

290
00:22:16,540 --> 00:22:18,577
the way you acted
today is a complete turnoff.

291
00:22:26,300 --> 00:22:26,740
Wang Hai,

292
00:22:28,044 --> 00:22:29,780
the three of us have
come this far together,

293
00:22:29,780 --> 00:22:31,555
and we've always been
honest with each other.

294
00:22:31,980 --> 00:22:33,180
If I ever do get with Er Jiu,

295
00:22:33,180 --> 00:22:34,400
you'll be the first to know.

296
00:22:36,140 --> 00:22:37,020
And whatever happens,

297
00:22:37,020 --> 00:22:38,466
don't hide it from Er Jiu or me.

298
00:22:44,700 --> 00:22:45,220
You?

299
00:22:47,940 --> 00:22:48,500
Got it.

300
00:22:49,380 --> 00:22:49,740
Come on.

301
00:22:51,022 --> 00:22:52,410
Madam, get me three bottles.

302
00:22:52,420 --> 00:22:53,020
(Mengtong Internet Cafe)

303
00:22:53,180 --> 00:22:53,822
Coming right up.

304
00:23:17,060 --> 00:23:17,620
Cheers.

305
00:23:29,088 --> 00:23:30,466
What are you two laughing at?

306
00:23:30,600 --> 00:23:32,540
I got hit so hard
that I can't even lift my head.

307
00:23:39,622 --> 00:23:41,140
Just drink straight from the bottle.

308
00:23:41,140 --> 00:23:43,288
I'm still bleeding.
How am I supposed to do that?

309
00:24:10,511 --> 00:24:11,933
Good morning, Ms. Lin.

310
00:24:17,180 --> 00:24:17,740
Ms. Lin,

311
00:24:18,980 --> 00:24:19,820
Mr. Fan is here.

312
00:24:20,140 --> 00:24:21,266
He's already downstairs.

313
00:24:21,820 --> 00:24:22,380
Mr. Fan?

314
00:24:31,780 --> 00:24:32,644
Help me take this in.

315
00:24:46,860 --> 00:24:47,660
Morning, Mr. Fan.

316
00:24:51,580 --> 00:24:52,980
You look pretty good today.

317
00:24:53,340 --> 00:24:53,820
Not bad.

318
00:24:54,500 --> 00:24:56,020
What brings you here so early?

319
00:24:56,466 --> 00:24:58,355
I was actually thinking
of going to your place

320
00:24:58,400 --> 00:24:59,666
and waiting downstairs for you.

321
00:25:00,140 --> 00:25:00,860
What's going on?

322
00:25:01,740 --> 00:25:03,380
I heard you ran into a bit of trouble.

323
00:25:03,580 --> 00:25:04,620
I've been quite worried.

324
00:25:06,100 --> 00:25:07,740
Looks like if
something doesn't go wrong,

325
00:25:07,820 --> 00:25:09,733
I don't realize how
many people care about me.

326
00:25:10,460 --> 00:25:11,020
Who else?

327
00:25:11,660 --> 00:25:12,260
A friend.

328
00:25:13,380 --> 00:25:13,700
Here.

329
00:25:14,740 --> 00:25:16,340
Your problem is my problem.

330
00:25:16,420 --> 00:25:18,060
That's not the first time
I've said that.

331
00:25:19,500 --> 00:25:21,580
You helped me with the Gu Yan situation,

332
00:25:22,180 --> 00:25:23,100
but this time,

333
00:25:23,540 --> 00:25:25,460
Dingqi Platform
might not be able to help.

334
00:25:25,580 --> 00:25:27,780
Didn't your authors just get poached?

335
00:25:28,300 --> 00:25:29,940
Then, find new ones.

336
00:25:30,333 --> 00:25:31,266
New writers, right?

337
00:25:31,333 --> 00:25:32,733
As long as you're willing to look,

338
00:25:32,740 --> 00:25:33,777
there are plenty out there.

339
00:25:33,977 --> 00:25:34,620
In this area,

340
00:25:34,620 --> 00:25:36,380
our platform's big data can help you.

341
00:25:38,140 --> 00:25:38,740
Also,

342
00:25:39,020 --> 00:25:40,820
the funding Zhiyuan promised you before

343
00:25:41,140 --> 00:25:43,060
wasn't that much anyway.

344
00:25:43,420 --> 00:25:44,020
I'll cover it.

345
00:25:48,422 --> 00:25:49,466
With money in place

346
00:25:49,660 --> 00:25:50,800
and a pool of newcomers,

347
00:25:51,022 --> 00:25:52,444
what else are you worried about?

348
00:25:54,911 --> 00:25:56,860
What does Dingqi Platform
want from Chenxing?

349
00:25:57,340 --> 00:25:59,260
A company as good as yours,

350
00:25:59,820 --> 00:26:00,980
we...

351
00:26:03,060 --> 00:26:03,700
want everything.

352
00:26:07,460 --> 00:26:08,940
That's not possible.

353
00:26:13,540 --> 00:26:14,200
Look,

354
00:26:14,740 --> 00:26:16,060
He Han is gone,

355
00:26:17,780 --> 00:26:18,460
Zhao Lanxin

356
00:26:18,980 --> 00:26:19,620
and Ling Yikai

357
00:26:20,580 --> 00:26:21,180
are gone, too.

358
00:26:22,860 --> 00:26:24,140
Running Chenxing on your own

359
00:26:24,660 --> 00:26:25,660
must be exhausting.

360
00:26:26,340 --> 00:26:27,900
And it's not just for a while.

361
00:26:28,300 --> 00:26:29,900
It'll stay that way.

362
00:26:30,180 --> 00:26:31,380
Originally,

363
00:26:31,380 --> 00:26:33,540
you were already
producing content for Dingqi.

364
00:26:33,820 --> 00:26:35,420
Why not just come over

365
00:26:35,911 --> 00:26:37,222
and become a subsidiary?

366
00:26:37,333 --> 00:26:39,044
I'll provide both funding and support.

367
00:26:39,580 --> 00:26:41,980
Your company will
definitely do better than it is now.

368
00:26:42,088 --> 00:26:43,177
What do you think?

369
00:26:44,700 --> 00:26:45,300
And...

370
00:26:46,060 --> 00:26:47,700
I'll give you shares in Dingqi.

371
00:26:53,400 --> 00:26:54,700
No need to reply right away.

372
00:26:55,780 --> 00:26:56,780
But this offer

373
00:26:57,420 --> 00:26:59,100
will remain open to you.

374
00:26:59,740 --> 00:27:00,180
Also,

375
00:27:00,780 --> 00:27:02,090
I think highly of Gu Yan.

376
00:27:02,090 --> 00:27:02,860
I'll support him.

377
00:27:03,340 --> 00:27:03,780
Thank you.

378
00:27:04,580 --> 00:27:05,500
I'll think about it.

379
00:27:12,580 --> 00:27:13,260
Do you

380
00:27:13,980 --> 00:27:15,180
have other plans?

381
00:27:16,220 --> 00:27:17,300
Besides Dingqi,

382
00:27:17,820 --> 00:27:20,340
other platforms have also shown
interest in working with us.

383
00:27:20,340 --> 00:27:22,420
But we're the biggest
platform in the industry.

384
00:27:30,660 --> 00:27:32,900
Platform size is important to us,
of course,

385
00:27:33,700 --> 00:27:36,820
but for a content company like ours,

386
00:27:37,420 --> 00:27:39,380
the cooperation model matters more.

387
00:27:41,100 --> 00:27:42,220
Can you tell me

388
00:27:42,860 --> 00:27:44,900
which platform is competing with us?

389
00:27:45,044 --> 00:27:46,155
That's not convenient to say.

390
00:28:00,500 --> 00:28:01,180
Hello, Sir.

391
00:28:02,380 --> 00:28:02,940
Where is he?

392
00:28:03,820 --> 00:28:04,620
I'm not sure.

393
00:28:04,888 --> 00:28:05,980
He's probably already left.

394
00:28:06,111 --> 00:28:07,511
I've already informed the front desk.

395
00:28:08,700 --> 00:28:09,560
Our manager is here.

396
00:28:10,300 --> 00:28:11,020
Hello, Mr. He.

397
00:28:11,180 --> 00:28:11,860
He's checked out?

398
00:28:12,260 --> 00:28:12,580
Right.

399
00:28:12,580 --> 00:28:14,540
That's actually why I came to see you.

400
00:28:14,900 --> 00:28:16,740
Your father has probably already left,

401
00:28:17,100 --> 00:28:19,380
but the room hasn't been paid for yet.

402
00:28:21,540 --> 00:28:22,380
Put it on my tab.

403
00:28:22,900 --> 00:28:23,220
Alright.

404
00:28:23,866 --> 00:28:25,222
Okay, go ahead with your work.

405
00:28:40,700 --> 00:28:43,700
If you take a taxi,

406
00:28:43,860 --> 00:28:45,177
it should take about ten minutes.

407
00:28:46,420 --> 00:28:48,140
If he really went to a nursing home,

408
00:28:48,460 --> 00:28:50,860
and it's indeed this one,

409
00:28:52,540 --> 00:28:54,300
you should call and ask.

410
00:28:55,980 --> 00:28:56,860
What should I say?

411
00:28:57,060 --> 00:28:58,020
Say I'm his son?

412
00:28:58,620 --> 00:29:00,300
He told them he's alone,

413
00:29:00,500 --> 00:29:01,460
with no family.

414
00:29:08,088 --> 00:29:09,555
Why were you looking for me?

415
00:29:12,220 --> 00:29:13,820
Dingqi plans to acquire Chenxing.

416
00:29:17,711 --> 00:29:20,022
If Lin Zhanqiao wanted to sell,
she would've done it already.

417
00:29:20,580 --> 00:29:22,180
But Mr. Fan offered a high price,

418
00:29:22,460 --> 00:29:24,860
well above Chenxing's current valuation.

419
00:29:25,180 --> 00:29:26,260
Chenxing has Gu Yan.

420
00:29:26,260 --> 00:29:28,420
That did stir things up for a while,

421
00:29:28,860 --> 00:29:30,420
but he's still new.

422
00:29:30,540 --> 00:29:31,540
His consistency

423
00:29:31,540 --> 00:29:33,420
hasn't stood the test of time yet.

424
00:29:35,220 --> 00:29:37,020
Mr. Fan never makes a losing deal.

425
00:29:37,340 --> 00:29:38,933
So why do you think he's doing this?

426
00:29:39,460 --> 00:29:41,660
Where did you hear this? Is it reliable?

427
00:30:12,780 --> 00:30:13,940
Let me make this clear first.

428
00:30:13,940 --> 00:30:15,940
I came this early because
I have something to say.

429
00:30:16,660 --> 00:30:18,900
I'm definitely not here
to check up on you.

430
00:30:20,900 --> 00:30:22,660
What is it

431
00:30:22,660 --> 00:30:25,340
that made you come at 7 AM?

432
00:30:27,820 --> 00:30:29,780
I'm planning to acquire Chenxing.

433
00:30:32,740 --> 00:30:33,340
Surprised?

434
00:30:38,177 --> 00:30:39,540
What does that have to do with me?

435
00:30:43,300 --> 00:30:46,020
Have He Han and Lin Zhanqiao
been in touch recently?

436
00:30:50,060 --> 00:30:50,900
Honestly,

437
00:30:51,140 --> 00:30:53,300
I'm surprised
they've stayed broken up this long.

438
00:30:54,060 --> 00:30:55,020
You probably don't know,

439
00:30:56,060 --> 00:30:58,460
but they break up and get back together

440
00:30:58,460 --> 00:30:59,780
at least once a year.

441
00:31:00,340 --> 00:31:02,311
Usually, it doesn't
last more than a week.

442
00:31:02,711 --> 00:31:04,555
We've all been through this,
so we get it.

443
00:31:04,660 --> 00:31:05,711
In situations like that,

444
00:31:05,980 --> 00:31:07,300
they'll never truly separate.

445
00:31:08,300 --> 00:31:08,660
Right?

446
00:31:10,580 --> 00:31:11,580
Unlike us,

447
00:31:11,933 --> 00:31:13,822
no fights or drama, just negotiation.

448
00:31:14,333 --> 00:31:16,933
Even after breaking up,
we can still meet like a normal pair.

449
00:31:17,140 --> 00:31:18,180
People like us,

450
00:31:18,700 --> 00:31:20,020
once it's over, it's really over.

451
00:31:22,555 --> 00:31:24,820
Sounds like you don't
actually want them to stay apart.

452
00:31:24,980 --> 00:31:26,940
I don't really care.

453
00:31:27,620 --> 00:31:30,020
They're known as
the golden couple in this circle.

454
00:31:30,155 --> 00:31:32,488
Of course, everyone
hopes they end up together.

455
00:31:36,200 --> 00:31:37,577
I don't care either way.

456
00:31:37,733 --> 00:31:38,955
Go on. I'll brush my teeth.

457
00:31:39,860 --> 00:31:40,940
You really don't care?

458
00:31:46,355 --> 00:31:49,488
Whether they get back together
doesn't affect your role as a manager.

459
00:31:50,620 --> 00:31:52,540
Personally, I think the three of you

460
00:31:53,540 --> 00:31:54,940
might end up forming a strong trio.

461
00:32:00,100 --> 00:32:02,980
So the money you're putting
into Lin Zhanqiao's company,

462
00:32:03,220 --> 00:32:04,300
you're betting

463
00:32:04,820 --> 00:32:06,540
that she and He Han
will get back together,

464
00:32:07,300 --> 00:32:08,100
and that He Han

465
00:32:08,622 --> 00:32:09,700
will return to Chenxing?

466
00:32:12,820 --> 00:32:14,580
I trust my judgment when it

467
00:32:15,380 --> 00:32:16,260
comes to people.

468
00:32:26,460 --> 00:32:28,180
So should I go tell Lin Zhanqiao?

469
00:32:28,260 --> 00:32:30,820
That depends on
how much you care about her.

470
00:32:31,540 --> 00:32:33,260
If it's like what Mr. Fan said,

471
00:32:33,900 --> 00:32:35,220
then you should be honest with me.

472
00:32:36,100 --> 00:32:37,860
I need to negotiate terms with him.

473
00:32:44,300 --> 00:32:44,740
I do care,

474
00:32:45,420 --> 00:32:46,660
but not as much as you think.

475
00:32:51,377 --> 00:32:52,822
Would you go back to Chenxing?

476
00:32:54,660 --> 00:32:55,140
No.

477
00:32:57,022 --> 00:32:57,980
Then, that settles it.

478
00:32:58,220 --> 00:33:00,540
Just treat it like gossip
and leave it at that.

479
00:33:03,980 --> 00:33:05,700
Alright, I'll have
Ms. Lin sign it later.

480
00:33:05,977 --> 00:33:08,044
Dingqi Platform knew
we lost several new authors.

481
00:33:08,244 --> 00:33:09,377
They have sent us some

482
00:33:09,400 --> 00:33:11,220
independent writers
recommended by their data.

483
00:33:11,340 --> 00:33:12,460
They're not bad.

484
00:33:12,600 --> 00:33:14,266
Reach out to them individually.

485
00:33:14,420 --> 00:33:15,866
Zhangzhu, contact this author.

486
00:33:15,955 --> 00:33:17,266
I've already interviewed him.

487
00:33:17,300 --> 00:33:18,740
Have him do a trial piece,

488
00:33:18,800 --> 00:33:20,890
and start discussing
contract details at the same time.

489
00:33:20,940 --> 00:33:21,300
Okay.

490
00:33:21,422 --> 00:33:23,580
Also, Gu Yan has been
invited to Dingqi Author Night.

491
00:33:25,060 --> 00:33:25,580
Nice.

492
00:33:26,100 --> 00:33:26,900
He's earned himself

493
00:33:26,900 --> 00:33:28,260
a place in the industry.

494
00:33:28,900 --> 00:33:29,380
Let him know

495
00:33:29,555 --> 00:33:30,666
to make a strong appearance.

496
00:33:30,700 --> 00:33:30,980
Got it.

497
00:33:40,900 --> 00:33:43,620
(Zhanqiao: What time will you
be back tonight? Emergency.)

498
00:33:45,740 --> 00:33:46,100
Hello.

499
00:33:46,444 --> 00:33:47,733
Here, give me a hand.

500
00:33:49,780 --> 00:33:50,180
Careful.

501
00:33:53,355 --> 00:33:54,488
A little thank-you fee.

502
00:33:54,620 --> 00:33:56,859
Thanks for lending me
this furniture to dress the place up.

503
00:33:56,860 --> 00:33:57,688
Is this enough?

504
00:33:58,355 --> 00:33:59,777
What are you doing this afternoon?

505
00:33:59,900 --> 00:34:00,860
Nothing much. Why?

506
00:34:01,044 --> 00:34:02,311
I'll take you somewhere.

507
00:34:04,820 --> 00:34:05,740
Two thousand,

508
00:34:05,860 --> 00:34:07,044
and you spent it on this?

509
00:34:08,380 --> 00:34:09,660
Two thousand isn't enough.

510
00:34:09,780 --> 00:34:11,111
I'll add some more for you.

511
00:34:11,177 --> 00:34:13,044
How long has it been
since you did your hair?

512
00:34:13,444 --> 00:34:14,400
I don't remember.

513
00:34:16,888 --> 00:34:19,644
You've been busy with the company
and Ling Yikai's issues all the time.

514
00:34:19,820 --> 00:34:21,488
You haven't left any time for yourself.

515
00:34:21,977 --> 00:34:23,420
What do I need time for myself for?

516
00:34:23,644 --> 00:34:24,740
Isn't that a waste of time?

517
00:34:25,020 --> 00:34:27,044
Don't you ever look at
yourself in the mirror?

518
00:34:27,088 --> 00:34:28,420
How much do you dislike yourself?

519
00:34:28,620 --> 00:34:30,844
The person in the mirror
isn't necessarily the real you.

520
00:34:31,020 --> 00:34:32,533
You look in the mirror every day.

521
00:34:32,622 --> 00:34:34,577
You understand what
I mean better than I do.

522
00:34:38,300 --> 00:34:39,180
Seven million.

523
00:34:40,820 --> 00:34:42,260
I think you're being too reckless.

524
00:34:42,780 --> 00:34:43,888
Please wait a moment.

525
00:34:48,180 --> 00:34:49,820
When you go all in and fail,

526
00:34:50,260 --> 00:34:51,340
people call you reckless.

527
00:34:51,940 --> 00:34:52,580
If you succeed,

528
00:34:53,020 --> 00:34:54,620
they'll call you bold,

529
00:34:54,900 --> 00:34:56,180
confident, and visionary.

530
00:34:56,580 --> 00:34:57,220
Seven million.

531
00:34:57,820 --> 00:34:59,380
Lin Zhanqiao's five new authors

532
00:34:59,460 --> 00:35:01,244
are now all with Colorful Culture Media.

533
00:35:04,100 --> 00:35:04,580
Also,

534
00:35:04,977 --> 00:35:07,444
Ling Yikai and I are planning
to get married by the end of the year.

535
00:35:07,820 --> 00:35:08,500
Married?

536
00:35:09,820 --> 00:35:10,580
Or engaged?

537
00:35:11,020 --> 00:35:11,580
Married.

538
00:35:12,066 --> 00:35:13,622
What's the point of
just getting engaged?

539
00:35:13,888 --> 00:35:15,460
Married, with a marriage certificate.

540
00:35:15,580 --> 00:35:16,340
Just that simple.

541
00:35:16,900 --> 00:35:17,860
All for seven million?

542
00:35:19,820 --> 00:35:20,820
Not for seven million.

543
00:35:21,660 --> 00:35:22,540
For his grandmother.

544
00:35:23,340 --> 00:35:24,222
His grandmother?

545
00:35:25,900 --> 00:35:27,220
When he was with you,

546
00:35:27,460 --> 00:35:29,260
he never told you about her, did he?

547
00:35:30,100 --> 00:35:32,380
We were only together
for less than two months.

548
00:35:32,955 --> 00:35:35,160
There were a lot of things
we didn't get to talk about.

549
00:35:36,660 --> 00:35:38,020
It's not about time.

550
00:35:38,500 --> 00:35:39,580
He wouldn't have told you.

551
00:35:40,200 --> 00:35:42,755
He was afraid you'd look down
on his background and family.

552
00:35:43,580 --> 00:35:46,020
But there's nothing he can't tell me.

553
00:35:47,300 --> 00:35:48,860
Either it scares me off,

554
00:35:49,660 --> 00:35:50,460
or if it doesn't,

555
00:35:50,980 --> 00:35:52,860
it becomes something that bonds us.

556
00:36:08,580 --> 00:36:09,820
Sorry, Mr. He Han,

557
00:36:10,580 --> 00:36:12,020
my boss has suddenly called a meeting.

558
00:36:12,577 --> 00:36:13,622
I'm a few minutes late.

559
00:36:13,860 --> 00:36:14,460
Go ahead, eat.

560
00:36:18,111 --> 00:36:19,060
I'm dying of thirst.

561
00:36:21,288 --> 00:36:23,460
Mr. He Han, didn't you also have
something to ask me?

562
00:36:23,460 --> 00:36:24,060
What is it?

563
00:36:24,660 --> 00:36:25,460
I wanted to ask...

564
00:36:26,940 --> 00:36:29,220
For those authors
Zhao Lanxin poached earlier...

565
00:36:29,980 --> 00:36:31,700
How did the list get leaked?

566
00:36:31,700 --> 00:36:32,500
Have you found out?

567
00:36:33,420 --> 00:36:33,900
Not yet.

568
00:36:34,780 --> 00:36:35,660
No, about that list,

569
00:36:35,660 --> 00:36:36,900
besides you and your boss,

570
00:36:37,140 --> 00:36:38,533
who else in the company knew?

571
00:36:40,460 --> 00:36:41,940
Mantou,

572
00:36:42,620 --> 00:36:44,140
Fragile, and Naobaijin.

573
00:36:50,711 --> 00:36:53,600
On Mr. Fan's side, he'll be recommending
some new authors to you soon.

574
00:36:53,911 --> 00:36:55,266
Do you want me to help you pick?

575
00:36:57,900 --> 00:36:58,980
Thank you, Mr. He Han.

576
00:36:59,580 --> 00:37:00,700
I almost felt awkward asking.

577
00:37:00,733 --> 00:37:02,177
There's nothing awkward about it.

578
00:37:02,180 --> 00:37:04,022
It'll be faster if the two
of us choose together.

579
00:37:09,860 --> 00:37:11,780
I have a question for you, Mr. He Han.

580
00:37:12,200 --> 00:37:13,460
Right, you were looking for me.

581
00:37:13,940 --> 00:37:14,780
What is it? Go ahead.

582
00:37:15,420 --> 00:37:15,860
So,

583
00:37:16,700 --> 00:37:18,980
when you helped me
screen authors before,

584
00:37:21,260 --> 00:37:23,140
was it actually to quietly help my boss?

585
00:37:24,060 --> 00:37:24,660
Of course.

586
00:37:32,060 --> 00:37:32,780
No wonder.

587
00:37:34,820 --> 00:37:35,780
Is it not to your taste?

588
00:37:35,860 --> 00:37:37,355
- I can order something else...
- No.

589
00:37:37,420 --> 00:37:38,620
It's really good, really.

590
00:37:38,977 --> 00:37:39,977
Go ahead and eat.

591
00:37:47,980 --> 00:37:49,170
I'll go buy some desserts later.

592
00:37:49,180 --> 00:37:50,800
Do you want me to
bring some back for you?

593
00:37:50,940 --> 00:37:52,060
No need. I have dinner plans.

594
00:38:20,420 --> 00:38:20,860
Thanks.

595
00:38:25,155 --> 00:38:26,533
What are you looking at?

596
00:38:28,460 --> 00:38:29,140
Nothing.

597
00:38:29,511 --> 00:38:30,810
Thought I saw someone I know,

598
00:38:30,810 --> 00:38:31,740
but I must be mistaken.

599
00:38:33,220 --> 00:38:34,540
You're not. That's Ling Yikai.

600
00:38:38,780 --> 00:38:39,700
Then, who's that woman?

601
00:38:40,100 --> 00:38:40,620
No idea.

602
00:38:40,755 --> 00:38:43,133
Probably someone he just
met at a bar these past few days.

603
00:38:43,666 --> 00:38:44,711
You don't care?

604
00:38:44,980 --> 00:38:46,100
No need. Let him be.

605
00:38:46,622 --> 00:38:48,244
He just wants to get
a reaction out of me.

606
00:38:48,300 --> 00:38:49,777
I'm not going to give him that.

607
00:38:50,340 --> 00:38:51,300
Zhao Lanxin,

608
00:38:52,060 --> 00:38:53,740
I underestimated you back in school.

609
00:38:54,780 --> 00:38:56,860
Maybe I've just improved
over the past few years.

610
00:39:02,020 --> 00:39:03,420
I really don't get Zhao Lanxin.

611
00:39:03,420 --> 00:39:05,088
Why would she put
herself through all that?

612
00:39:05,311 --> 00:39:06,920
It's better to stay single
than date a man

613
00:39:06,940 --> 00:39:07,620
like Ling Yikai.

614
00:39:09,511 --> 00:39:12,111
Because she's seen how Ling Yikai was
when he was chasing you,

615
00:39:12,155 --> 00:39:13,844
like he would give up
everything for you.

616
00:39:14,533 --> 00:39:15,740
So it's not that he doesn't know

617
00:39:15,740 --> 00:39:16,955
how to treat a woman well,

618
00:39:17,220 --> 00:39:19,260
it's that Zhao Lanxin knows very clearly

619
00:39:19,940 --> 00:39:20,780
that in his eyes,

620
00:39:21,220 --> 00:39:23,380
she's not the one
worth treating that way.

621
00:39:23,955 --> 00:39:25,377
That's why she can't accept it.

622
00:39:26,660 --> 00:39:27,500
I told her,

623
00:39:28,140 --> 00:39:30,100
as long as she suddenly
stops being good to him,

624
00:39:30,460 --> 00:39:32,777
I guarantee Ling Yikai will
come running back to her.

625
00:39:33,620 --> 00:39:34,300
Sometimes,

626
00:39:34,740 --> 00:39:35,820
it's not about who's better,

627
00:39:36,140 --> 00:39:37,380
but who cares less.

628
00:39:39,900 --> 00:39:41,200
But she doesn't believe it.

629
00:39:41,333 --> 00:39:42,577
Actually, she just doesn't dare.

630
00:39:42,820 --> 00:39:44,340
But today, you dared, with Mr. Fan.

631
00:39:44,860 --> 00:39:46,420
So for now, you have the upper hand.

632
00:39:47,540 --> 00:39:48,780
Today, I really was

633
00:39:49,380 --> 00:39:51,140
bluffing my way through it.

634
00:39:52,444 --> 00:39:54,460
What other platforms
would want to work with me?

635
00:39:55,460 --> 00:39:57,260
The whole industry
is struggling right now.

636
00:39:57,780 --> 00:39:59,955
Big or small,
every platform is barely staying afloat.

637
00:40:00,700 --> 00:40:02,300
What cooperation opportunities?

638
00:40:03,220 --> 00:40:04,020
There aren't any.

639
00:40:05,420 --> 00:40:06,900
So now it all comes down to acting.

640
00:40:08,740 --> 00:40:09,820
If you sell to Mr. Fan now,

641
00:40:09,955 --> 00:40:11,133
he'll slash your price.

642
00:40:11,466 --> 00:40:13,620
You need to keep it up
until he doubles his offer.

643
00:40:18,580 --> 00:40:19,540
Otherwise,

644
00:40:20,200 --> 00:40:22,311
how about you help me
find a few investment firms,

645
00:40:22,420 --> 00:40:24,333
have them come and put on a show for me?

646
00:40:26,200 --> 00:40:28,300
Didn't you say there's
a mole in your company?

647
00:40:29,600 --> 00:40:30,488
What about it?

648
00:40:40,755 --> 00:40:42,066
Use it to your advantage.

649
00:40:42,220 --> 00:40:44,340
Chenxing's ability to develop authors

650
00:40:44,340 --> 00:40:45,844
is widely recognized in the industry.

651
00:40:46,300 --> 00:40:47,980
Not only have we cultivated

652
00:40:47,980 --> 00:40:49,533
top authors like He Han and Gu Yan,

653
00:40:49,622 --> 00:40:52,422
but we also place great importance
on developing mid-tier writers,

654
00:40:52,466 --> 00:40:54,260
such as Hong Qigong and Zhugan Dalan,

655
00:40:54,660 --> 00:40:55,860
who are all well known.

656
00:40:56,340 --> 00:40:58,460
At the same time,
we continue to discover

657
00:40:58,460 --> 00:40:59,460
promising new authors,

658
00:40:59,980 --> 00:41:01,620
building our own creative pipeline

659
00:41:02,100 --> 00:41:03,620
based on innovation and content.

660
00:41:03,620 --> 00:41:04,620
Ms. Lin isn't done yet?

661
00:41:04,955 --> 00:41:06,700
We've been waiting
for over half an hour.

662
00:41:07,700 --> 00:41:08,900
I'm sorry.

663
00:41:08,900 --> 00:41:10,380
Mr. Chen, let me first

664
00:41:10,380 --> 00:41:12,420
give you a brief
overview of our company.

665
00:41:12,820 --> 00:41:14,340
She should be done shortly.

666
00:41:14,340 --> 00:41:15,820
Highly capable signed authors,

667
00:41:15,866 --> 00:41:17,540
a steady stream of creative content,

668
00:41:17,660 --> 00:41:20,060
and a professional
and efficient editorial team.

669
00:41:20,660 --> 00:41:21,860
These are the core strengths

670
00:41:21,860 --> 00:41:22,860
of Chenxing

671
00:41:23,300 --> 00:41:24,500
and the reason we remain

672
00:41:24,620 --> 00:41:26,900
at the top tier of
revenue in the industry.

673
00:41:27,100 --> 00:41:28,100
I'm Ms. Lin's assistant.

674
00:41:28,300 --> 00:41:29,460
I'll be hosting you today.

675
00:41:30,866 --> 00:41:31,610
This way, please.

676
00:41:31,620 --> 00:41:31,980
Alright.

677
00:41:34,460 --> 00:41:35,500
Please, Mr. Chen, this way.

678
00:41:35,700 --> 00:41:36,020
Come.

679
00:41:36,300 --> 00:41:36,980
Thank you.

680
00:41:37,060 --> 00:41:37,755
You're welcome.

681
00:41:38,100 --> 00:41:39,300
Ms. Lin, this is Mr. Chen.

682
00:41:39,420 --> 00:41:40,180
Hello.

683
00:41:40,180 --> 00:41:40,540
Ms. Lin.

684
00:41:40,660 --> 00:41:41,330
Please see them out.

685
00:41:41,340 --> 00:41:42,250
- Alright.
- Take care, Mr. Liu.

686
00:41:42,260 --> 00:41:43,100
This way, please.

687
00:41:43,820 --> 00:41:45,260
Please wait here for a moment.

688
00:41:45,260 --> 00:41:46,180
Ms. Lin is a bit busy.

689
00:41:46,180 --> 00:41:47,020
She'll be right over.

690
00:41:47,533 --> 00:41:49,130
If possible,
we'll increase our investment.

691
00:41:49,140 --> 00:41:49,540
Okay.

692
00:41:49,540 --> 00:41:50,990
Please contact us again.
This way, please.

693
00:41:51,020 --> 00:41:52,460
Mr. Liu, thank you
for your hard work today.

694
00:41:52,460 --> 00:41:53,700
- Not at all.
- Thank you.

695
00:41:53,700 --> 00:41:54,380
Thank you.

696
00:41:54,380 --> 00:41:55,100
Alright.

697
00:41:55,620 --> 00:41:56,900
We'll see you next time, Mr. Liu.

698
00:41:56,933 --> 00:41:57,930
- Goodbye.
- Take care.

699
00:41:57,940 --> 00:41:59,260
Let me revise it and get back to you.

700
00:41:59,420 --> 00:41:59,820
Mr. Liu.

701
00:41:59,820 --> 00:42:01,088
Mr. Liu, hello, please come in.

702
00:42:01,340 --> 00:42:02,140
Have a seat inside.

703
00:42:03,422 --> 00:42:04,460
You've looked into it?

704
00:42:05,460 --> 00:42:08,100
I found out that today, representatives
from three investment firms

705
00:42:08,180 --> 00:42:09,644
went to Chenxing for discussions.

706
00:42:09,711 --> 00:42:10,460
Among them,

707
00:42:10,460 --> 00:42:12,020
Hongyuan is the largest,

708
00:42:12,066 --> 00:42:13,644
and Lin Zhanqiao spent the most time

709
00:42:13,688 --> 00:42:15,220
talking with their representative.

710
00:42:15,300 --> 00:42:16,990
Did they mention
how much they're offering?

711
00:42:17,020 --> 00:42:18,355
I don't know the exact figure.

712
00:42:20,540 --> 00:42:21,060
Thanks.

713
00:42:21,800 --> 00:42:23,100
Ms. Lin, we'll be heading out now.

714
00:42:23,100 --> 00:42:23,460
Goodbye.

715
00:42:26,340 --> 00:42:28,460
♪Please don't call my name♪

716
00:42:29,460 --> 00:42:31,620
(Mr. Fan)

717
00:42:32,900 --> 00:42:35,100
♪Let my feet take me where they will♪

718
00:42:38,900 --> 00:42:41,020
♪She needs independence♪

719
00:42:41,080 --> 00:42:42,210
Thank you for your hard work.

720
00:42:42,220 --> 00:42:43,133
You can leave early.

721
00:42:44,133 --> 00:42:45,880
- Thank you, Ms. Lin.
- Thank you, Ms. Lin.

722
00:42:47,580 --> 00:42:49,140
♪Or be just a decoration♪

723
00:42:50,540 --> 00:42:50,940
Hello?

724
00:42:51,822 --> 00:42:52,940
Did everything go smoothly?

725
00:42:53,660 --> 00:42:55,340
Better than I could've hoped.

726
00:42:56,300 --> 00:42:57,860
I bet Mr. Fan is at home right now,

727
00:42:57,860 --> 00:42:59,340
pulling his hair out.

728
00:43:01,060 --> 00:43:02,460
I wish it were all real.

729
00:43:05,921 --> 00:43:07,041
(I've been thinking.)

730
00:43:08,321 --> 00:43:11,601
(Everyone's most comfortable level of intimacy)

731
00:43:12,361 --> 00:43:19,691
(is probably different.)

732
00:43:20,691 --> 00:43:22,441
♪If the sky♪

733
00:43:22,951 --> 00:43:24,351
♪And the sea♪

734
00:43:24,891 --> 00:43:26,601
♪Turned upside down♪

735
00:43:28,161 --> 00:43:30,091
♪If a swimming fish♪

736
00:43:30,491 --> 00:43:33,881
♪Fell in love with a flying bird♪

737
00:43:35,651 --> 00:43:37,621
♪If back then♪

738
00:43:37,981 --> 00:43:42,391
♪We had never let go♪

739
00:43:42,991 --> 00:43:49,271
♪We wouldn't be lost in the crowd♪

740
00:43:50,391 --> 00:43:52,541
♪We met in a thirteenth month♪

741
00:43:52,541 --> 00:43:54,411
♪Held each other in a fifth season♪

742
00:43:54,591 --> 00:43:57,031
♪And found our way back whole♪

743
00:43:57,871 --> 00:44:00,041
♪So let this surging love♪

744
00:44:00,041 --> 00:44:04,471
♪Rise like tides that never fall♪

745
00:44:05,371 --> 00:44:07,551
♪If we're caught in a pouring rain♪

746
00:44:07,551 --> 00:44:08,641
♪That's alright♪

747
00:44:09,181 --> 00:44:09,931
♪If we're buried♪

748
00:44:09,931 --> 00:44:12,631
♪By passing years all the better♪

749
00:44:12,891 --> 00:44:15,071
♪At least we still can keep♪

750
00:44:15,251 --> 00:44:19,671
♪This one eternal photograph♪

751
00:44:35,431 --> 00:44:37,721
♪We're on misaligned tracks♪

752
00:44:37,721 --> 00:44:39,481
♪Running in opposite ways♪

753
00:44:39,601 --> 00:44:42,071
♪Searching all along the way♪

754
00:44:42,871 --> 00:44:45,031
♪For the fire of our younger hearts♪

755
00:44:45,221 --> 00:44:50,131
♪And the beauty lost in time♪

756
00:44:50,131 --> 00:44:53,651
♪This time don't lose each other again♪

757
00:44:53,891 --> 00:44:54,861
♪Only after loss♪

758
00:44:54,861 --> 00:44:57,491
♪Do we learn what truly matters most♪

759
00:44:57,901 --> 00:45:00,261
♪In another time and space♪

760
00:45:00,261 --> 00:45:01,821
♪We'll stay and walk together♪

761
00:45:01,821 --> 00:45:04,651
♪Till we grow old♪

762
00:45:05,611 --> 00:45:07,901
♪But still the sky will never♪

763
00:45:07,901 --> 00:45:10,571
♪Turn with the sea♪

764
00:45:13,091 --> 00:45:15,501
♪But still a swimming fish won't♪

765
00:45:15,501 --> 00:45:20,711
♪Fall in love with a flying bird♪
